Standard Products Q3 net falls after charge . Standard Products Co said Tuesday its earnings in the third quarter ended March 31 included a charge to cover the previously announced closing of two automotive parts plants in New York and Kentucky . The company reported net income of $ 515 , 000 , or $ 0 . 03 a share , down from $ 7 . 3 million , or $ 0 . 43 , a year ago . Sales climbed to $ 281 . 8 million from $ 277 . 3 million last year . The pre - tax charge related to the plant closings totaled $ 17 . 7 million , or $ 0 . 63 a share , Standard Products said . The company said the closings are proceeding on schedule . Standard Products makes sealing , trimming and vibration control systems for the automotive and other industries . ( ( Chicago newsdesk ( 312 ) 408 - 8787 ) ) 
